0"><p>Quantios is a global leader in SaaS solutions for the Wealth, Trust, =
and Corporate Services (TCSP) industry. Focused on driving digital transfor=
mation, Quantios provides advanced technology that ensures seamless complia=
nce and efficient administration. Our solutions empower businesses to strea=
mline operations and focus on growth.</p><p>The TCSP industry is undergoing=
 rapid consolidation and increasing regulatory scrutiny, making data integr=
ity more critical than ever. Quantios leverages AI, automation, and advance=
d technology to manage data with precision, supporting growth, compliance, =
and operational efficiency for over 600 clients globally.</p><p>Join a team=
 of 300+ professionals across 12 offices worldwide, and be part of a compan=
y driving transformation in over 80 international jurisdictions, where your=
 <strong>innovative problem-solving and AI-enabled analytical capabilities =
</strong>will help shape the future of this fast-changing industry.</p><p>A=
 Problem Management Specialist serves as a strategic problem-solver who ide=
ntifies root causes of recurring incidents, prevents future disruptions, an=
d drives continuous improvement through <strong>AI-powered analytics, innov=
ative thinking, and proactive problem resolution</strong>.</p><p>The Proble=
m Management Specialist (L2) is a critical role in this evolution. With Lev=
el 1 inquiries increasingly handled by AI deflection, the L2 specialist ser=
ves as the technical authority for complex, high-value investigations. This=
 role combines deep-tier systems engineering with cutting-edge AI orchestra=
tion to eliminate systemic issues, reduce incident volumes, and ensure the =
long-term stability of our global SaaS platforms.</p><p><strong>Job Respons=
ibilities:</strong><br><br><strong>AI-Driven RCA &amp; Deep Troubleshooting=
</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead complex investigations across Microsoft Busine=
ss Central, IIS, APIs, and SQL environments.</p><p>Use AI platforms (e.g., =
Windsurf, Cursor) to analyze IIS logs, HTTPERR logs, and telemetry for hidd=
en issue patterns.</p></li><li><p>Conduct structured blameless post-mortems=
 (5 Whys, Fishbone, Fault Tree Analysis) to identify true root causes.</p><=
/li><li><p>Perform SQL forensics (SQL Profiler, Query Store) and review AL/=
.NET/API code to resolve recurring incidents.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Proac=
tive Prevention &amp; Automation</strong></p><ul><li><p>Build predictive mo=
nitoring dashboards using historical incident data.</p></li><li><p>Leverage=
 Generative AI (GitHub Copilot, Claude) to develop PowerShell/Python automa=
tion scripts.</p></li><li><p>Validate AI-generated fixes before production =
deployment.</p></li><li><p>Implement permanent solutions to reduce repeat i=
ncidents and backlog.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Knowledge Engineering &amp; C=
ollaboration</strong></p><ul><li><p>Own and enhance an AI-powered Known Err=
or Database (KEDB).</p></li><li><p>Transform technical findings into struct=
ured, searchable knowledge articles using NLP tools.</p></li><li><p>Partner=
 with L3/Product teams to eliminate issues at source-code level.</p></li></=
ul><p><strong>Innovation &amp; Leadership</strong></p><ul><li><p>Advocate A=
I adoption, mentor teams on AI tools and prompt engineering.</p></li><li><p=
>Drive innovation initiatives and pilot emerging AIOps platforms.</p></li><=
/ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Degree in Financial=
 Technology, Computer Science, IT, or related field (or equivalent experien=
ce).</p></li><li><p><strong>Strong experience in AI-driven root cause analy=
sis and deep troubleshooting within SaaS environments.</strong></p></li><li=
><p>Expertise in IIS (ARR, thread pool optimization, timeout configuration)=
 and advanced SQL (query optimization, execution plans, SQL Profiler).</p><=
/li><li><p><strong>Ability to debug AL, .NET, or similar languages and trou=
bleshoot APIs, databases, and cloud architectures.</strong></p></li><li><p>=
Hands-on experience with diagnostic tools (ProcMon, Fiddler/Wireshark, brow=
ser developer tools).</p></li><li><p>Proficiency in AI development tools (C=
ursor, Windsurf, GitHub Copilot) and prompt engineering for log analysis.</=
p></li><li><p>Experience in automation scripting (PowerShell/Python), predi=
ctive monitoring, and validating AI-generated solutions.</p></li><li><p>Fam=
iliarity with Power BI or analytics platforms for trend visualization.</p><=
/li><li><p>Understanding of fintech products and basic ITIL concepts (prefe=
rred).</p></li><li><p>Strong collaboration skills, proactive mindset, and w=
illingness to work shift rotations if required.</p></li></ul><p><br></p></d=
